Description: Shoulder sherd of Milesian Fikellura pottery small neck-amphora; interior reserved; exterior, worn white slip: on shoulder, open cable pattern above dividing band of gear pattern between traces of dilute bands; below, dot reticulation with dot rosettes as filling ornament.
Curator's comments: 'Naukratis 1886' is written in ink on the interior surface of the sherd.
Bibliographic references: CVA British Museum 8 / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum: Great Britain 13, British Museum 8 (p. 9, no. 14, pl. 8, no. 14)
Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p. 247, no. 2)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.044)
